---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base
  title="About"
  description="Latch is built by one operator who got tired of inbox triage being a job. Hosted on Cloudflare. Solo and serious."
>
  <section class="section hero">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow reveal reveal-1">About</span>
      <h1 class="reveal reveal-2">A small tool with strong opinions.</h1>
      <p class="lead reveal reveal-3">
        Latch is built by one person for the kind of operator who'd rather have
        a few small tools that do one thing well than one platform that does
        everything badly. If you've ever opened a "productivity suite" and
        closed it again, you're our user.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section about">
    <div class="container about-grid">
      <div>
        <h2>The bet.</h2>
        <p class="lead">
          The bet is that nobody really wants Inbox Zero. What people actually
          want is the confidence that nothing important is rotting in there. A
          surfaced thread, drafted reply, and a quiet morning is worth more
          than a count that says "0."
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2>The constraints.</h2>
        <ul class="constraints">
          <li>One product. No suite, no platform, no second app.</li>
          <li>One accent color. Restraint is the brand.</li>
          <li>Your data, your DO. Per-account isolation, no cross-tenant learning.</li>
          <li>Honest exits. One click deletes the model.</li>
          <li>No dark mode in v0. We'll get there in v1.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section about">
    <div class="container about-grid">
      <div>
        <h2>The infrastructure.</h2>
        <p class="lead">
          Latch is built on Cloudflare. Workers handle the request edge,
          Durable Objects hold per-account state, and Email Sending delivers
          the morning summary. The result is a stack that's fast at the edge,
          private by isolation, and cheap enough to give Solo away.
        </p>
        <p class="footnote">
          Marketing site on Cloudflare Pages. Source is public on
          <a class="btn-link" href="https://github.com/isaaclins/latch" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2>The person.</h2>
        <p class="lead">
          Hi — I'm Isaac. I build Latch alone right now. I read every support
          email myself. If you write to me you'll get a reply from me, not a
          ticketing bot. The fastest way to reach me is
          <a class="btn-link" href="mailto:contact@isaaclins.com">contact@isaaclins.com</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section cta-strip">
    <div class="container cta-row">
      <div>
        <h2>Want to try it?</h2>
        <p class="lead">The Solo tier is free. The Operator tier has a 14-day trial. There's no waitlist.</p>
      </div>
      <a href="/pricing" class="btn btn-primary">See pricing</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .hero h1 { margin-block: 16px 20px; max-width: 22ch; }

  .about-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 56px;
  }
  @media (max-width: 820px) { .about-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 32px; } }

  .about h2 { font-size: 1.5rem; margin-block-end: 14px; }

  .constraints {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    display: grid;
    gap: 12px;
  }
  .constraints li {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--hairline);
    padding-block-start: 12px;
    color: var(--ink-2);
  }
  .constraints li:first-child { border-top: 0; padding-block-start: 0; }

  .footnote {
    margin-block-start: 16px;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--ink-3);
  }

  .cta-strip { background: var(--canvas-2); }
  .cta-row {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 40px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .cta-row h2 { margin-block-end: 8px; }
</style>
